{{Quote|Just because something’s not happening to you, doesn’t mean it’s not happening.|Cassie Lang to [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
'''{{ConjecNameAU|Cassandra}} {{Conjecture|Eleanor}} "Cassie" Lang''' is the daughter of [[Scott Lang|Scott]] and [[Maggie Lang]]. Fascinated by the [[Quantum Realm]], Lang invented the [[Quantum Satellite]], which resulted in her, her father and the [[Janet van Dyne|van]] [[Wasp|Dyne]] [[Hank Pym|family]] being shrunken deep into the realm, being trapped in [[Axia]]. Wishing to aid the [[Freedom Fighters]] in spite of Ant-Man's denies, she donned a [[Cassie Lang's Suit|suit]] to battle against [[Kang's Empire]]. However, Cassie and Ant-Man were captured by [[M.O.D.O.K.]] and questioned by [[Kang the Conqueror]], who used her life as leverage for Ant-Man to retrieve the [[Multiversal Engine Core]]. Once she escaped, Cassie made a speech across Axia to motivate the oppressed citizens to [[Uprising in Axia|revolt]] against Kang and his army before facing off M.O.D.O.K. and returning home with her family.

==Biography==
{{MD|Cassandra Lang (Earth-199999)}}
===Father Figures===
====Biological Father in Prison====
Cassie Lang was born to [[Maggie Lang|Maggie]] and [[Scott Lang]] in [[2008|July 2008]].{{Ref|AM}}{{Ref|AMatW}}{{Ref|AMatWQ}} Her father was a petty thief who vowed to quit his life of crime when his daughter was born. In [[2012]], when Lang was three years old, however, her father was arrested after breaking into the house of the CEO of [[VistaCorp]] and sending back money the company had stolen from its customers. While her father was still in prison, Lang's parents divorced. Her mother soon became engaged to [[Jim Paxton]], who raised Lang like his own daughter.{{Ref|AM}} During this time Lang didn't lose touch with her biological father, with him sending Lang some of his favorite comic books in the mail. During her father's prison sentence, Lang would have her fourth birthday party, which was "{{WPS|Unicorns}} vs. [[Dragons]]" themed, and portrayed Tap-Dancing Tree #3 in a play.{{Ref|LOftLG}}

====Seventh Birthday Party====
[[File:Cassie hugs Scott.jpg |{{AltFloat}}|Lang is finally reunited with her [[Scott Lang|father]]]]
{{Quote|Daddy!"<br>"Peanut! Oh! Happy birthday! I'm so sorry I'm late, I didn't know what time your party started."<br>"It was on the invitation!|Cassie Lang and [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
[[2015|Three years later]], Cassie had a party for her seventh birthday. Her [[Scott Lang|father]] arrived, having been released from prison. Cassie was delighted to see him, and father and daughter hugged. He presented her with a gift of an ugly stuffed rabbit, which Lang instantly loved. Despite her father wishing to keep his brief visit a secret, an overexcited Lang went to inform her [[Maggie Lang|mother]] of his arrival; she promptly spat out her drink in surprise, which Cassie also happily informed her father of. Her mother and [[Jim Paxton]] then spoke to her father and, after talking in private, he left the party, waving goodbye to his daughter as she stood outside.{{Ref|AM}}

====Discussing Her Father====
[[File:Maggie and Cassie.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lang speaks to her [[Maggie Lang|mother]]]]
{{Quote|Mommy, is [[Scott Lang|Daddy]] a bad man? I heard some grown-ups talking. They said he was bad."<br>"No, he's not bad. Daddy just gets confused sometimes.|Cassie Lang and [[Maggie Lang]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
The night after the party, Cassie was being tucked into bed by her [[Maggie Lang|mother]], who asked if she really liked the gift her [[Scott Lang|father]] had given her; Cassie assured Maggie that she did because she loved the rabbit's incredible ugliness. Cassie then asked her mother if her father was a bad man because of the way she and [[Jim Paxton]] had spoken about him. However, her mother assured Cassie that her father was not, just complicated and easily confused.

The next morning, Cassie joined her mother and Paxton for breakfast and they discussed her father who had just broken out of prison, with Paxton given the task of tracking him down. Cassie asked if he was going to find her dad, to which Paxton told her he only wanted him to be safe. In response, Cassie told Paxton that she hoped he did not find Scott.{{Ref|AM}}

====Visit from Her Father====
[[File:ScottCassie-AntMan.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang is kissed by [[Ant-Man]] in her sleep]]
Another night, while Cassie was sleeping, her [[Scott Lang|father]] snuck into her bedroom. Happy at seeing his beloved daughter again, he continued to watch Cassie for a while before enlarging himself and kissing her forehead. Once he was satisfied with his moment of seeing his daughter, he left as Cassie continued to sleep.{{Ref|AM}}
{{Clear}}

===Saved by Ant-Man===
====[[Duel at Jim Paxton's House|Threatened by Yellowjacket]]====
[[File:Cassie monster AM.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang is held hostage by [[Yellowjacket]]]]
{{Quote|Are you a monster?"<br>"Do I look like a monster?"<br>"I want my [[Scott Lang|daddy]]!"<br>"I want your daddy too.|Cassie Lang and [[Yellowjacket]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
Without warning one night, Cassie's [[Jim Paxton's House|home]] was attacked by [[Darren Cross]], who was wearing a weaponized [[Yellowjacket Suit]]; Cross threw her [[Maggie Lang|mother]] out the house and took Cassie hostage in her bedroom, telling her that he wanted to find and kill her [[Scott Lang|father]]. She questioned if Yellowjacket was a monster, something which the supervillain did not deny.{{Ref|AM}} In her head Lang wanted to say "I only care if you're a monster on the inside" but instead she asked for her father. Later, in her essay ''[[My Daddy, My Hero]]'', Cassie would later recall that she thought that Yellowjacket's costume looked silly.{{Ref|LOftLG}}
[[File:Antman 09256.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lang learns that her father is [[Ant-Man]]]]
Coming to her rescue, her father arrived moments later in the [[Ant-Man Suit]] and battled Cross, both shrinking down to minuscule sizes and fighting on Cassie's {{WPS|Thomas the Tank Engine}} toy train set. Cassie watched in shock as tiny explosions occurred on her train set where the two fought and hundreds of [[Ants|ants]] arrived and attacked Yellowjacket seemingly under her father's command. Even more shocking was when her father used a [[Pym Particle Discs|device]] which caused her Thomas the Tank Engine figure to instantly grow to gigantic sizes as well as [[Giant Pet Ant|one of the ants]], which grew to the size of a large [[Dogs|dog]]. The toy figure burst out of the house, creating destruction and a huge gaping hole.
[[File:SLang-HuggingCLang-AM.jpeg|{{AltFloat}}|Lang hugging her [[Ant-Man|father]] after the battle]]
When [[Jim Paxton]] arrived, he tried to bring Cassie to safety, but Yellowjacket cornered them and attempted to kill them both. With only one chance left to save them, her father then shrunk down to the smallest size possible and attacked Cross, shrinking into his Yellowjacket Suit and damaging its internal mainframe, causing the suit to crush into itself and cause both of them to [[Quantum Realm|disappear]]. Cassie called out to her father repeatedly, while getting back in her bed. Once he returned in a series of flashing lights, Cassie hugged her father tightly. Shortly after as the [[San Francisco Police Department|police officers]] rushed up to her room, Cassie watched her father make his exit as Ant-Man before hugging her mother. Cassie then adopted the enlarged ant as her pet.{{Ref|AM}}

====Family Dinner====
[[File:Cassie Dinner -AM.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang has dinner with her whole family]]
{{Quote|I did my first cartwheel today."<br>"Yeah, she has been practicing all week."<br>"Sweetie, that's pretty amazing, peanut.|Cassie Lang, [[Maggie Lang]] and [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man (film)}}
Later, Cassie had her whole family together for a dinner, after [[Jim Paxton]] and her [[Maggie Lang|mother]] invited her [[Scott Lang|father]] over to show their gratitude for everything he had done to protect their family. Paxton even informed her father that he would not be going back to jail after breaking free the last time. Her father thanked him and asked what was going on in their lives, in which Cassie told him she did a cartwheel and her mother chimed in that she had been practicing gymnastics. Cassie gave her [[Giant Pet Ant|pet ant]] pieces of food from under the table. Paxton then showed her father a video of her doing so. As her father congratulated her, he then received a call on his phone and made a quick exit, kissing Cassie on the head as he left.{{Ref|AM}}

===Father's Return===
====Visiting Her Father====
{{Quote|Hey, you try and entertain a ten year old when you can't leave the house. You know the lengths that I've gone to? Close-up magic. I learned that."<br>"Why can't you just leave my daddy alone?|[[Scott Lang]] and Cassie Lang to [[Jimmy Woo]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
Later, Cassie was reunited with [[Scott Lang|her father]] after he returned home.{{Ref|AIWP1}} She frequently visited her father at his [[Scott Lang's House|house]] during his two-year sentence of house arrest. They played together as he tried to keep Cassie entertained without having to leave the house along with [[Luis]] who came sometimes to play with them.{{Ref|AMatW}}
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 150.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lang playing with her [[Ant-Man|father]]]]
One day in [[2018]], Cassie played with her [[Scott Lang|father]] in a tunnel that he had made out of cardboard boxes for them to crawl through as they go in search of treasure. The treasure turned out to be her father's "World's Greatest Grandma" trophy that Cassie gave to him. Lang asked if she can take it for show-and-tell at school, but her father refused. They then "escaped" down stairs that had been converted into a slide and ran into the fence. However, her father accidentally put his foot through the perimeter.
[[File:Antman-wasp-movie-screencaps.com-964.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lang speaks with [[Jimmy Woo]]]]
The [[FBI]] then arrived to search the place just as Cassie's [[Maggie Lang|mother]] and [[Jim Paxton]] came to pick her up. Lang questioned why the FBI were there and asked Agent [[Jimmy Woo]] why he couldn't leave her father alone. Woo tried to explain to Lang the reason due to Lang allying with [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] in [[Germany]] and violating the [[Sokovia Accords]], but Lang wasn't convinced. After the FBI left, Lang left with her mother but promised to come back. Cassie secretly kept the "World's Greatest Grandma" trophy with her for show-and-tell.{{Ref|AMatW}}

====Wanting to be a Hero====
[[File:Cassie covers for Scott.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang covers for [[Ant-Man|her father]]]]
{{Quote|Trying to help people isn't dumb."<br>"Well, I screw it up just about every time."<br>"So maybe you just need someone watching your back. Like a partner.|Cassie Lang and [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp}}
Cassie called [[Ant-Man|her father]] looking for her soccer shoes, not knowing that he was currently being held captive. As a result, she went to his house to look for the shoes. The [[FBI]] arrived just after learning that her father wasn't in his house. Cassie went upstairs and found [[Scott Lang's Replacement Ant|an enlarged ant]] in the bathtub. She went back downstairs and tried to prevent [[Jimmy Woo]] and the other FBI agents from going upstairs by claiming that her father was sick. Luckily, her father made it home in time so as to not raise suspicion.
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 35.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lang and her [[Ant-Man|father]] talk about being a hero]]
After the agents left, Cassie and her father had a conversation about him being Ant-Man again. She told him that he needs a partner to watch his back. He found out that she was referring to herself. He refused, explaining that if he let her help it would make him the worst parent. Later, back at her mother's house, she smiled as she witnessed her father, as [[Giant-Man]], on a news report on television.
[[File:Ant-Man and the Wasp 09.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Lang hugging her recently released [[Ant-Man|father]]]]
Cassie was soon met by her father at her house, after having been let out of house arrest. She hugged him which led to Paxton and her mother hugging him too. That night, Cassie met [[Hope van Dyne]] and shrunk down via [[Pym Particles]] for the first time with her father and van Dyne, as they sat in a shrunken car watching the movie ''{{WPS|Them! (1954 film)|Them!}}'' on a laptop.{{Ref|AMatW}}

===Losing Her Father===
====[[Snap]]====
{{Quote|I know how to take care of myself, okay? Trust me. I'm pretty good at it by now.|Cassie Lang to [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
Cassie survived the [[Snap]], and when her [[Scott Lang|father]] was nowhere to be found, she believed he had disintegrated. She also became aware that [[Hope van Dyne]] and her [[Hank Pym|par]][[Janet van Dyne|ents]] had disintegrated. With this loss of those close to her at a young age, Cassie was forced to become self-reliant.{{Ref|AE}}

==== Learning about the Quantum Realm====
{{Quote|Okay, so when you were all, like, [[Snap|gone]] those five years, I had a lot of time. And I started reading [[Hank Pym|Grandpa Hank]]'s old journals, and I got really into the [[Quantum Realm]].|Cassie Lang to [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
While her [[Scott Lang|father]] was gone, along with half of the entire population, Cassie came across [[Hank Pym]]'s journals, which intrigued her. Cassie's main interest was in the [[Quantum Realm]], and she spent a lot of her time researching into it.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====Reunited with Her Father====
[[File:Scott & Cassie.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang is reunited with her [[Ant-Man|father]]]]
{{Quote|Cassie?"<br>"Dad?"<br>"...You're so big!|[[Scott Lang]] and Cassie Lang|Avengers: Endgame}}
In [[2023|October 2023]], five years after the [[Snap]], Cassie, who was now a fifteen year old, answered the door of her [[Jim Paxton's House|house]] to find her [[Scott Lang|father]] standing outside. She was shocked but overjoyed to discover that he was alive, and together they shared an emotional reunion.{{Ref|AE}}
[[File:Hope van Dyne, Scott Lang & Cassie Lang.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang with [[Ant-Man|her father]] and [[Wasp|Hope van Dyne]]]]
Cassie filled her father in on what had happened since he disappeared, informing him of [[Thanos]] and how he used the [[Infinity Stones]] to [[Snap|wipe out]] half of all life. After learning this, Scott left his daughter to seek the [[Avengers]]' help reversing the Snap. Later, following the [[Blip]], Cassie reunited with her father and a restored [[Hope van Dyne]] outside her house. The three of them watched fireworks celebrating the return of the population.{{Ref|AE}}

===Adventure in the Quantum Realm===
====Using Pym Particles====
{{Quote|You know, I promised your [[Maggie Lang|mom]] that you would only use [[Pym Particles|this stuff]] when one of [[Wasp|us]] was around. It's really dangerous tech.|[[Scott Lang]] to Cassie Lang|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
Over the next three years, Cassie got close with [[Hope van Dyne]], who became a mother-figure to her, and [[Hank Pym]] and [[Janet van Dyne]], who became grandparent-figures to her. Wishing to learn more about Pym's research, Cassie came to him with questions, and he helped her with her curiosity, even allowing her access to [[Pym Particles]]. This was made aware to Cassie's parents, so [[Scott Lang]] made a promise to her [[Maggie Lang|mother]] that she would only use the tech in his or Hope's presence. However, Cassie would go behind her father's back, and had a [[Cassie Lang's Suit|suit]] created for her without his knowledge. This secrecy between Lang and her father grew, as she would at one point end up in jail briefly, which was only known by Pym, as well as working with Pym and Hope to build a [[Quantum Satellite]].{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====Family Dinner====
[[File:Cassie Lang released from jail.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang in the [[San Francisco Police Station]]]]
{{Quote|Look, you wanna help. I get it. I do, Cassie. I really do. But I don't want you wasting your life."<br>"At least I'm still trying to to do something with mine.|[[Scott Lang]] and Cassie Lang|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
Lang joined a group of protestors to support those being cleared out of a homeless shelter by the police. However, things escalated and the police used tear gas on the protestors, so Lang used a [[Pym Particle Discs|Pym Particle Disc]] to shrink a police car. This got her arrested and taken to [[San Francisco Police Station]].
[[File:Cassie in car.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang arguing about her recent behavior]]
Lang would later be bailed out and picked up by [[Scott Lang]] and [[Hope van Dyne]], who had been called by the police. As Lang was leaving, she returned the shrunken car. During the drive, Scott voiced his disappointment with her, but she defended her actions, which her father understood. When Scott mentioned her possibly losing the [[Pym Particles|Pym Particle]] tech, Lang let it slip out that she had a [[Cassie Lang's Suit|suit]], which shocked Scott, who claimed that he wanted her to have a normal life, so Lang recalled when [[Yellowjacket]] tried to kill her.
[[File:Serving pizza.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang having dinner at the [[Pym Residence]]]]
They then arrived at [[Hank Pym]] and [[Janet van Dyne]]'s [[Pym Residence|house]] for a family dinner. As they all sat at the table, Pym asked Lang about her time in jail, revealing that it wasn't her first time. Scott decided to address his daughter's desire to make a difference, stating that he didn't want her wasting her life, but she responded by calling him out for not doing anything anymore. This then led Scott to learn about Lang working with Pym and Hope, so she excitedly decided to show him what they had been doing.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====Trapped in the Quantum Realm====
[[File:Quantumania Trailer (10).png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang presenting the [[Quantum Satellite]]]]
{{Quote|Where are we?|Cassie Lang to [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
They all went down to [[Hank Pym]]'s lab, where Lang showed her [[Scott Lang|father]] the [[Quantum Satellite]] she built with Pym and [[Hope van Dyne]]. Lang explained how it worked, commenting on how she could have used it to find her father when he was trapped in the Quantum Realm for five years, and Scott told her how impressed he was.
[[File:Quantumania Trailer (30).png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang being pulled into the [[Quantum Realm]]]]
[[Janet van Dyne]] expressed concern about their creation due to the [[Quantum Realm]] being dangerous, but Lang explained that they wouldn't enter it. But when Janet learned that it sent a signal down to the Quantum Realm, she panicked and shut down the device. Before she could explain herself, a portal opened up and began pulling them all in. Lang held onto her father, but she quickly was sucked into the portal, entering the Quantum Realm. She was saved by her father, who went in after her and grew to giant size to soften her fall.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====Meeting the Freedom Fighters====
[[File:Cassie and Scott Lang.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang looks around the [[Quantum Realm]]]]
{{Quote|We gathered who we could to fight. It was never enough."<br>"I'm sorry."<br>"We can help.|[[Jentorra]], [[Scott Lang]] and Cassie Lang|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
Realising that they were in the [[Quantum Realm]], [[Scott Lang]] tried to assure Lang that they would be fine, but they were soon attacked by [[Sun Beasts|giant]] creatures. They were saved when an energy blast destroyed the second creature chasing them, and the two then found themselves surrounded by people who took them captive.
[[File:Cassie and her dad.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang at the [[Freedom Fighters]]'s camp]]
Lang and her father were taken to a camp, where they were forced to drink the [[Ooze]], which allowed them to be able to understand the people from the Quantum Realm. They were then questioned by [[Quaz]], who suspected them of being spies, so they explained where they were from and how they got in the Quantum Realm, which Quaz accepted, having the ability to read minds. [[Jentorra]] arrived and warned them about [[Kang the Conqueror]], so Quaz read their minds and found that they knew nothing about him or anything to do with their situation.
[[File:Cassie wants to help.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang wants to help the [[Freedom Fighters]]]]
They followed Jentorra, who explained how Kang had destroyed their homes, which forced some of them to fight back, forming the [[Freedom Fighters]], but they have only lost against him. This saddened Lang to hear, so she told Jentorra that they could help them. Scott spoke with his daughter in private, trying to get her to focus on getting themselves back home, noting that they had no idea how much time could go by while they were in the Quantum Realm. Lang was disappointed in her father not caring about helping the Freedom Fighters.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====[[Attack on the Freedom Fighters|Attacked by M.O.D.O.K.]]====
[[File:Cassie with her dad.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang witnesses [[Jentorra]] being attacked]]
{{Quote|Look, momentum, right? Jump, tap, right? One move. Jump, tap."<br>"I know how to do it, Dad.|[[Ant-Man]] and Cassie Lang|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
Upon learning they knew [[Janet van Dyne]], [[Jentorra]] ordered Lang and [[Scott Lang]] to be sent far away from the camp, as [[Kang the Conqueror]] would be coming for them. At that moment, the camp was ambushed, so Lang ran away with her father. As they hid, Lang witnessed Jentorra being attacked, so she put on her [[Cassie Lang's Suit|suit]] and rushed over to help her.
[[File:Ant-Man & Stinger.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang and [[Ant-Man]] meeting [[M.O.D.O.K.]]]]
However, not having a lot of experience fighting in the suit, Cassie found it difficult to defeat some of the enemies and had to be saved by her father. Ant-Man told her the technique to fighting when growing to normal size. As many of the [[Freedom Fighters]] were being captured, Cassie and Ant-Man were targeted by an unknown attacker. They were confronted by the attacker, and were surprised to discover that it was [[Darren Cross]], who had become a giant head, now going by M.O.D.O.K. M.O.D.O.K. fired a blast at them, incapacitating them, and he took them as prisoners.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====The Conqueror's Prisoner====
[[File:Cassie in Kang's prison.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang sitting in a cell in the [[Quantum Realm]]]]
{{Quote|Let me make this easy for you. You will bring me what I need or I will kill your daughter in front of you, then make you relive that moment over and over again in time, endlessly, until you beg me to kill you. Do we understand?|[[Kang the Conqueror]] to [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
As they sat in their cells, [[Scott Lang]] tried to lighten the mood by comparing how many times they had both been in jail. They were then joined by [[M.O.D.O.K.]], who explained how he ended up in the Quantum Realm. M.O.D.O.K. then told Lang that he discovered her signal and used it to bring them into the [[Quantum Realm]].
[[File:Cassie hurt by Kang.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang being tortured by [[Kang the Conqueror]]]]
[[Kang the Conqueror]] arrived, and Lang listened to him speak to her father, making him an offer to steal something for him to get them both out of the Quantum Realm. When Kang mentioned knowing how things end, Lang enquired about what he meant, and he explained that he knew how everything ended, being able to see all of time and that other versions of him needed to be stopped. Scott refused to help Kang, so he began to hurt Lang, forcing Scott to agree to help. They were both released from their cells and brought to a portal outside.
[[File:Cassie with Kang's Guard.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang watching her [[Ant-Man|father]] dive into the [[Multiversal Engine Core|Core]]]]
Lang, being escorted by [[Quantumnauts]], followed her father through the portal, where they saw the [[Multiversal Engine Core]] before them. As Scott prepared to shrink it down to size, Lang got free from the Quantumnauts and hugged her father. Lang apologized, saying that it was her fault they were in this mess, but Scott comforted Lang by telling her that his whole life happened because of him messing up and that she was the only thing that he did right. Lang was then pulled away from her father, but not before he gave her a [[Pym Particle Discs|shrink and grow disc]].{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====[[Uprising in Axia]]====
[[File:Cassie shrinks.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang escapes from the [[Quantumnauts]]]]
{{Quote|Come to the [[Celestium|tower]]! Fight back! I know you've been waiting. Now is the time to strike back. [[Kang the Conqueror|He]] knows he can't take all of us.|Cassie Lang|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
Once her [[Scott Lang|father]] successfully shrunk the [[Multiversal Engine Core]], Lang was taken back to be put in her cell by two [[Quantumnauts]]. However, as they walked down a hallway, Lang used the [[Pym Particle Discs|discs]] on the Quantumnauts and escaped from them by shrinking herself and running away.
[[File:Cassie's motivational speech.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang inspires the [[Axia]] citizens to fight back]]
Lang made her way to the cell [[Jentorra]] was being kept in to rescue her. Lang was found by a group of Quantumnauts, and she was able to defeat them all and open the cell. Jentorra told Lang that they needed to get a message out to anyone who could fight and free the rest of the [[Freedom Fighters]]. Lang and Jentorra were able to interrupt [[Kang the Conqueror]]'s broadcast, and Lang gave a speech to the citizens of [[Axia]], telling them that despite their history of loss, they could still fight back against Kang if they were all united.
[[File:Cassie in her suit.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang facing off against [[M.O.D.O.K.]]]]
Cassie and Jentorra then returned to the cells and began freeing the Freedom Fighters. [[M.O.D.O.K.]] arrived, so Cassie told Jentorra to free the rest of the prisoners as she dealt with M.O.D.O.K. Cassie was chased by M.O.D.O.K. outside and was eventually cornered. M.O.D.O.K. taunted Cassie by saying that her father wasn't around to save her. But at that moment, they witnessed Giant-Man and [[Wasp]] arrive, which distracted M.O.D.O.K. and allowed Cassie to escape by shrinking. As she ran away, Cassie witnessed the citizens of Axia arrive and fight Kang's army.
[[File:Cassie redeems MODOK.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang attempting to redeem [[M.O.D.O.K.]]]]
When Cassie saw her father struggling to get past Kang's shield, she went to help him, but was stopped by M.O.D.O.K., who began charging at her. With nowhere else to run, Cassie took a grow disc, put it in the regulator of her [[Cassie Lang's Suit|suit]] and grew to giant form. She punched M.O.D.O.K., causing him to go flying backwards, unable to get back up. Cassie went to leave, but upon hearing M.O.D.O.K. pathetically call out to her, she returned and told him to stop being bad, stating it was never too late be redeemed.
[[File:Ant-Man, Wasp and Stature.png|{{AltFloat}}|Cassie standing with [[Ant-Man]] and [[Wasp]]]]
Still in giant form, Cassie reunited with her father, and they both hugged and talked about how it felt being that big. They then returned to normal size and were joined by Wasp, and the three rushed to the [[Celestium]] to confront Kang. Cassie initially stood back as Ant-Man and Wasp attacked Kang, and when he's back was to her, Cassie grew to giant form and grabbed Kang, but he quickly broke free of her. As they recovered from the fight, Kang began ranting at them about how powerful he was, only for an army of [[ants]] and M.O.D.O.K. to arrive and overwhelm Kang, defeating him.
[[File:Cassie and Hank.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang waits for her [[Ant-Man|father]] to come through]]
As a result of him disabling Kang's shield, M.O.D.O.K. was fatally injured. He told Lang that she was right about him being able to change, and they all awkwardly watched as M.O.D.O.K. slowly died. [[Janet van Dyne]] informed them that she opened a portal, so they rushed to it, with Janet, [[Hank Pym]], and Hope going in first. Before Lang could go through, Scott pushed into the portal to save her. Back in Pym's lab, they all waited for Scott to return, with Hope going back for him, but the portal closed. Fortunately, Lang was able to open it again, and Scott and Hope made it through safely.{{Ref|AMatWQ}}

====Back to Normal====
[[File:Ant Family Dinner.png|{{AltFloat}}|Lang having dinner with her family]]
{{Quote|It's not my birthday."<br>"I know. But I missed a few.|Cassie Lang and [[Scott Lang]]|Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania}}
